<h1 class="centre">Entering Greek</h1>
<p>
<div class="indent">
This program uses an English keyboard setting for entering Greek. The letters are mapped as follows:

Where a Greek letter has an English equivalent just type the English letter. For this purpose 'f' is equivalent to phi.
<br /><br />
<table  >
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>a</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&alpha;</p>
		</td>
		<td class="tdmid" rowspan="10"></td>
		<td  >
			<p>n</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&nu;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >

		<td  >
			<p>b</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&beta;</p>
		</td>

		<td  >
			<p>x</p>
		</td>
