<p>
For capitals use the Caps and Caps Lock keys as usual.
<p>
Other letters are entered using the left-hand Alt key as follows:

</p>
<table  cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" >
	<col width="128*">
	<col width="128*">
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-e</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&eta;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-k</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&chi;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-o</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&omega;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-p</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&psi;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-t</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&theta;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr >
		<td  >
			<p>Alt-s</p>
		</td>
		<td  >
			<p>&sigmaf;</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<p>
If a normal sigma is placed at the end of a word it will be corrected to a final sigma.
<p>
For a smooth breathing hold down 'v' while pressing the vowel/rho key or key combination. For a rough breathing hold down 'c'.
<p>
For iota subscript hold down the right-hand alt key ("alt gr"). As iota subscripts only apply to long vowels there is no need to press alt for eta or omega when using an iota subscript.
</p>
<p>
Accents are not supported.
</p>
